tldr: The user requested a plan to implement a database for questionnaire
  responses, an admin dashboard with CSV export, and an authentication system.
  The plan was implemented, including a simplified authentication using Next.js
  middleware, and all functionalities were successfully tested.
overview: The user wanted to extend a sleep questionnaire application to include
  database storage for responses, an admin dashboard for client access, and an
  authentication system. The project utilized NeonDB (PostgreSQL) with Prisma
  for data persistence. Initially, a custom session management system with
  HMAC-signed cookies was implemented for authentication. However, this was
  later streamlined by adopting Next.js middleware for route protection and a
  simpler cookie-based authentication, significantly reducing boilerplate code.
  The admin dashboard provides a table view of questionnaire responses and a CSV
  export feature. All implemented functionalities, including database
  interactions, API endpoints, authentication, and data export, were thoroughly
  tested and confirmed to be working as expected.
